text.tspan: Leave Belfast on the M2 northbound, then join the M5 signposted
Whiteabbey. At the end of the M5, go straight at the next two roundabouts
signposted 'Whiteabbey (A2)'. Stay on this road for 1.3 miles, and take the
left filter lane at the third set of traffic lights. Whiteabbey Presbyterian
is the large white church on the left.
Head on the A2 (Shore Road) towards Belfast for 4 miles, take the first right
after Loughshore Park onto Wood Grange. Drive through Whiteabbey
village. Whiteabbey Presbyterian is the large white church on the right.
Turn oﬀ at Junction 6 on the M1 and take the A49 towards Ballynahinch /
Saintﬁeld. Stay on this road for 4.4 miles, turn right down Bailliesmills road.
Follow this road for 0.9 miles until you see Larchﬁeld Estate Walls on your
right hand side. DO NOT take the 1st exit (Labelled Larchﬁeld Farm) but the
2nd Exit – on your right, opposite the Gate Lodge and signposted GUESTS.
12:30pm - Church Service at Whiteabbey Presbyterian Church
